# Language conventions

## User-facing → Spanish

Write in Spanish anything the end user sees or reads:

- API response bodies and `detail` / error messages returned to clients
- UI copy (Gradio labels, placeholders, buttons, tooltips)
- User-oriented documentation (README sections aimed at operators or end users)
- Prompts or messages shown in chat interfaces

## Everything else → English

Write in English:

- Source code (identifiers, string keys used only internally)
- Comments and inline notes
- Docstrings (module, class, function)
- Commit messages and developer-facing docs under `docs/`

## Examples

```python
# ❌ BAD — Spanish docstring
def ask(input_data: AskInput) -> dict:
    """Envía un mensaje a Jarvis."""

# ✅ GOOD — English docstring, Spanish user message
def ask(input_data: AskInput) -> dict:
    """Send a message to Jarvis and return the assistant reply."""
    if not input_data.message:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="El mensaje no puede estar vacío.")
```

```python
# ❌ BAD — English shown to the user in the UI
gr.Textbox(label="Your message")

# ✅ GOOD
gr.Textbox(label="Tu mensaje")
```
